==Introduction==
A '''Group''' widget allows to group related '''Properties''' and render them on View and Edit pages using different layouts:
* [[Help:Sections Layout|Sections Layout]]
* [[Help:Table Layout|Table Layout]]
* [[Help:Properties Layout|Properties Layout]]
* [[Help:Pivot Table Layout|Pivot Table Layout]]
* [[Help:Tabs Layout|Tabs Layout]]
* [[Help:Portal Layout|Portal Layout]]
* [[Help:Portal Column Layout|Portal Column Layout]]
* [[Help:Simple Layout|Simple Layout]]
* [[Help:Banner Layout|Banner Layout]]
* [[Help:Custom Layout|Custom Layout]]

A Group doesn't modify the structure of the database. It only changes rendering on the pages.

A Group might be embedded in other Groups, creating a multi-level hierarchy.

Each group in a hierarchy might use different layout type, which help to create sophisticated visualizations patterns.

The "custom" layout allow to define custom layout for the group using any MediaWiki syntax.
The custom layout should be used only when all other available layouts don't provide required visualization.

<span style="color:red">The '''Concept''' itself is a Group itself, which allows to apply one of the available layouts to the entire Concept.</span>

==Definition==
<pre>
<concept>
  <structure layout="{VIEW LAYOUT TYPE}" form="{FORM LAYOUT TYPE}" class="{CLASS}">
    <group name="{GROUP NAME}">
      <property name="Property 1">
      <property name="Property 2">
      <property name="Property 3">

      <group name="{GROUP NAME}" layout="{VIEW LAYOUT TYPE}" formLayout="{FORM LAYOUT TYPE}" class="{CLASS}">
        <property name="Property A">
        <property name="Property B">
        <property name="Property C">
        <customView>
          {CUSTOM LAYOUT TEMPLATE}
        </customView>
      </group>
    </group>

    <property name="Property I">
    <property name="Property II">

    <customView>
      {CUSTOM LAYOUT TEMPLATE}
    </customView>
  <structure>
</concept>
</pre>

{| class="helptable"
|-
! {GROUP NAME}
| A label of the Group.
|-
! style
| An optional section defining desired style to render a group of properties. If not specified, the "sections" layout is used.
|-
! {VIEW LAYOUT TYPE}
| A layout to be used to render group of properties on the '''View Page'''. The following options are allowed:
* '''sections'''. See [[Help:Sections Layout|Sections Layout]] for more details.
*	'''table'''. See [[Help:Table Layout|Table Layout]] for more details.
*	'''pivottable'''. See [[Help:Pivot Table Layout|Pivot Table Layout]] for more details.
*	'''properties'''. See [[Help:Properties Layout|Properties Layout]] for more details.
*	'''portal'''. See [[Help:Portal Layout|Portal Layout]] for more details.
*	'''portalcolumn'''. See [[Help:Portal Column Layout|Portal Column Layout]] for more details.
*	'''simple'''. See [[Help:Simple Layout|Simple Layout]] for more details.
*	'''tabs'''. See [[Help:Tabs Layout|Tabs Layout]] for more details.
Default value: "sections".
|-
! {EDIT LAYOUT TYPE}
| A layout to be used to render group of properties on the '''Edit Page'''. See the {VIEW LAYOUT TYPE} for a list of allowed values.
If the value is not specified it defaults to the {VIEW LAYOUT TYPE}.
|-
! {CUSTOM LAYOUT TEMPLATE}
| A template for a custom layout defined using MediaWiki syntax.
|-
! {CLASS}
| A CSS class to be applied to rendered group. See [[Project:Css]] page for more details. By default the following classes are enabled: cleartable, greytable, wikitable. Default value: "wikitable".
|}


==Example==
<pre>
<concept name="User" plural="Users" type="Dynamic" image="User.png" color="f9f9f9">
  <description></description>

  <structure layout="properties">
    <group name="Name" layout="table">
      <property name="Prefix" />
      <property name="First name" mandatory="true" />
      <property name="Last name" mandatory="true" />
    </group>
    <group name="Organization" layout="table">
      <property name="Organization"/>
      <property name="Function"/>
      <property name="Address"/>
    </group>
    <group name="Contact information" layout="pivottable">
      <property name="Telephone"/>
      <property name="Email"/>
    </group>
    <property name="Remarks"/>
  </structure>
</concept>
</pre>


